$pearl_page_personal_blog["fullwidth-post"] = array ( 'content' => '"Breakup cuts" are so common, almost every hairstylist has helped execute one. "A haircut after a breakup is powerful," Chase Kusero, hairstylist and co-founder of IGK, says. "People [often] keep their hair a certain way because of what a partner likes, or because it’s how they’ve always worn it. When you cut it and wear it how you want it, it’s empowering." That being said, it\'s important to make sure you\'re doing it for the right reasons. "When you do a cut out of anger or revenge and that anger fades, you want to make sure you still like the cut!" Franck, hairstylist and fellow co-founder of IGK, adds. <img class="alignleft wp-image-171 size-full" src="http://pearl.stylemixthemes.com/personal/wp-content/uploads/sites/14/2017/09/blog_image.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="460" />Coco Chanel once said "A woman who cuts her hair is about to change her life." Slightly-cheesy Pinterest quote aside, there\'s actually a lot of merit to this saying. (In 2017, the sentiment reads a little more like \'new hair, who dis?\') For a lot of people, that major change comes after the end of a relationship. Enter: the "breakup cut." The concept isn\'t new (and it\'s often stereotyped), but there is some scientific proof to it after all. "Hair is not only an aspect of your identity [and] self-expression, it\'s one of the few things you can control quite easily," Dr. Sanam Hafeez, clinical neuropsychologist and professor at Columbia University, tells Refinery29. "Changing your hair can be a big statement. It may mean you announcing something without announcing it or signify a metamorphosis. It\'s an instant statement that may actually make you feel like a new person." <div class="clearfix"></div> <blockquote>Process your emotions, sit with the pain, cry, get a trim, but don\'t make any drastic changes until it\'s passed — and it will pass.</blockquote> We know what you\'re thinking now: Is this really healthy, or just a quick fix? "Shedding your hair may not equal out to shedding your problems," Hafeez reminds us. "Process your emotions, sit with the pain, cry, get a trim, but don\'t make any drastic changes until it\'s passed — and it will pass." Ahead, six women tell the real stories behind their "breakup cuts" — and how it ended up being the best decision they could have made. <iframe src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/34019569&amp;color=0066cc" width="100%" height="166" frameborder="no" scrolling="no"></iframe> The hair pros agree: "It’s good to give yourself time to process and reflect before taking action," Jen Atkin, celebrity hairstylist and creator of Ouai Haircare, tells R29. "Yes, cutting your hair is a rush, so I can see why getting a great cut after a breakup can be exciting, but it doesn’t mean it has to be done in a rush." Her rule: If you still want the cut after a week, then do it. "It\'s an opportunity to reinvent yourself, so take your time deciding who you want to be next," she adds, "Then get rid of those bad feelings and move on!”', 'meta' => array ( '_vc_post_settings' => array ( 0 => 'a:1:{s:10:"vc_grid_id";a:0:{}}', 1 => 'a:1:{s:10:"vc_grid_id";a:0:{}}', ), '_wp_old_slug' => array ( 0 => 'try-these-takes-on-a-classic-button-up', 1 => 'try-these-takes-on-a-classic-button-up-2-4', ), '_thumbnail_id' => array ( 0 => '3436', ), 'slide_template' => array ( 0 => 'default', ), '_wpb_vc_js_status' => array ( 0 => 'false', ), 'page_title_box_align' => array ( 0 => 'center', ), 'page_title_box_title_size' => array ( 0 => 'h1', ), 'page_title_box_bg_color' => array ( 0 => 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.65)', ), 'page_title_box_bg_image' => array ( 0 => '39', ), 'page_title_box_text_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_box_line_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_box_subtitle_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_button_text' => array ( 0 => 'Button', ), 'page_title_button_url' => array ( 0 => '#', ), 'page_bc' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'page_title_breadcrumbs' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'page_title_box' => array ( 0 => '', ), 'page_title_box_title' => array ( 0 => '', ), 'page_title_box_subtitle' => array ( 0 => '', ), 'page_title_button' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'single_post_layout' => array ( 0 => '14', ), '_dp_original' => array ( 0 => '48', ), '_edit_last' => array ( 0 => '1', ), '_edit_lock' => array ( 0 => '1507186426:1', ), ), );
$pearl_page_personal_blog["video-post"] = array ( 'content' => '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]"Breakup cuts" are so common, almost every hairstylist has helped execute one. "A haircut after a breakup is powerful," Chase Kusero, hairstylist and co-founder of IGK, says. "People [often] keep their hair a certain way because of what a partner likes, or because it’s how they’ve always worn it. When you cut it and wear it how you want it, it’s empowering." That being said, it\'s important to make sure you\'re doing it for the right reasons. "When you do a cut out of anger or revenge and that anger fades, you want to make sure you still like the cut!" Franck, hairstylist and fellow co-founder of IGK, adds.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row equal_height="yes" content_placement="middle"][vc_column width="1/2" offset="vc_col-lg-5"][vc_single_image image="177" img_size="full"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" offset="vc_col-lg-5"][vc_column_text] <blockquote>I\'m not going to lie, I did cry a bit when they cut off the ponytail because I felt like I was letting go of my past — and there would be no more feeling sad or thinking about him.</blockquote> [/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]We know what you\'re thinking now: Is this really healthy, or just a quick fix? "Shedding your hair may not equal out to shedding your problems," Hafeez reminds us. "Process your emotions, sit with the pain, cry, get a trim, but don\'t make any drastic changes until it\'s passed — and it will pass." Ahead, six women tell the real stories behind their "breakup cuts" — and how it ended up being the best decision they could have made.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][stm_carousel_gallery images_effect="0" autoscroll="disable" thumbnails="disable" description="disable" pagination="disable" images="182,181,180,179,178" image_size="540x340" carousel_width="540px"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]The hair pros agree: "It’s good to give yourself time to process and reflect before taking action," Jen Atkin, celebrity hairstylist and creator of Ouai Haircare, tells R29. "Yes, cutting your hair is a rush, so I can see why getting a great cut after a breakup can be exciting, but it doesn’t mean it has to be done in a rush." Her rule: If you still want the cut after a week, then do it. "It\'s an opportunity to reinvent yourself, so take your time deciding who you want to be next," she adds, "Then get rid of those bad feelings and move on!”[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'meta' => array ( '_vc_post_settings' => array ( 0 => 'a:1:{s:10:"vc_grid_id";a:0:{}}', 1 => 'a:1:{s:10:"vc_grid_id";a:0:{}}', ), '_thumbnail_id' => array ( 0 => '3438', ), 'slide_template' => array ( 0 => 'default', ), '_wpb_vc_js_status' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'page_title_box_align' => array ( 0 => 'center', ), 'page_title_box_title_size' => array ( 0 => 'h1', ), 'page_title_box_bg_color' => array ( 0 => 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.65)', ), 'page_title_box_bg_image' => array ( 0 => '1716', ), 'page_title_box_text_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_box_line_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_box_subtitle_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_button_text' => array ( 0 => 'Button', ), 'page_title_button_url' => array ( 0 => '#', ), 'page_bc' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'single_post_video' => array ( 0 => 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KRsLLjlvLvE', ), 'single_post_video_preview' => array ( 0 => '175', ), 'disable_post_sidebar' => array ( 0 => '', ), '_dp_original' => array ( 0 => '41', ), '_edit_last' => array ( 0 => '1', ), '_wp_old_slug' => array ( 0 => '5-sporty-pieces-you-need-in-your-closet-4', ), '_edit_lock' => array ( 0 => '1507186739:1', ), ), );
$pearl_page_personal_blog["interview-post"] = array ( 'content' => '[vc_row][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_single_image source="featured_image" img_size="730x460" onclick="link_image"][vc_column_text]After all, the last year has kind of sucked: the U.S. elected a misogynistic president, reports of rampant sexism in Silicon Valley and at the nation\'s top law firms, and a continued lack of quality federal benefits that would help women advance in the workplace. It\'s easy to get depressed about the state of the world for women. <strong>Maria Anderson:</strong> <em>The concept isn\'t new, but there is some scientific proof to it after all?</em> <strong>Judith Ohikuare:</strong> "Hair is not only an aspect of your identity [and] self-expression, it\'s one of the few things you can control quite easily," Mrs. Selena Nooyi, clinical neuropsychologist and professor at California University, tells us. "Changing your hair can be a big statement. It may mean you announcing something without announcing it or signify a metamorphosis. It\'s an instant statement that may actually make you feel like a new person." <strong>M.A.:</strong> <em>But there are bright spots to be found, and one of the brightest is Fortune\'s annual Most Powerful Women List?</em> <strong>J.O.:</strong> I have naturally curly hair that I\'ve relaxed for over a decade. A friend was going natural and I wanted to join her, but in order to do so I would have to get a major cut. My boyfriend loved my long hair, so I chose not to cut it [while we were together]. I told my friend that I would join her in her natural hair journey... if I ever broke up with him.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row equal_height="yes" content_placement="middle"][vc_column width="1/12"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="199" img_size="350x460" onclick="link_image"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text] <blockquote>I\'m not going to lie, I did cry a bit when they cut off the ponytail because I felt like I was letting go of my past — and there would be no more feeling sad or thinking about him.</blockquote> [/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]<strong>M.A.:</strong> <em>We\'ve got 50 incredible examples of women shattering glass ceilings and helping a younger generation of women see how much you can accomplish when you dream big?</em> <strong>J.O.:</strong> It felt weird... like I was 100 pounds lighter. The best part of cutting it was that all of my friends immediately knew we had broken up. I didn\'t even have to explain myself. I think it was the right choice at the time, and I wanted to go natural anyway, so it was a win-win. After all, the last year has kind of sucked: the U.S. elected a misogynistic president, reports of rampant sexism in Silicon Valley and at the nation\'s top law firms, and a continued lack of quality federal benefits that would help women advance in the workplace. It\'s easy to get depressed about the state of the world for women. <strong>M.A.:</strong> <em>The concept isn\'t new, but there is some scientific proof to it after all?</em> <strong>J.O.:</strong> "Hair is not only an aspect of your identity [and] self-expression, it\'s one of the few things you can control quite easily," Mrs. Selena Nooyi, clinical neuropsychologist and professor at California University, tells us. "Changing your hair can be a big statement. It may mean you announcing something without announcing it or signify a metamorphosis. It\'s an instant statement that may actually make you feel like a new person."[/vc_column_text][stm_carousel_gallery images_effect="0" thumbnails="disable" description="disable" pagination="disable" images="201,202,203,204,205" image_size="540x340" carousel_width="540px"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]<strong>M.A.:</strong> <em>But there are bright spots to be found, and one of the brightest is Fortune\'s annual Most Powerful Women List?</em> <strong>J.O.:</strong> I have naturally curly hair that I\'ve relaxed for over a decade. A friend was going natural and I wanted to join her, but in order to do so I would have to get a major cut. My boyfriend loved my long hair, so I chose not to cut it [while we were together]. I told my friend that I would join her in her natural hair journey... if I ever broke up with him.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'meta' => array ( '_vc_post_settings' => array ( 0 => 'a:1:{s:10:"vc_grid_id";a:0:{}}', 1 => 'a:1:{s:10:"vc_grid_id";a:0:{}}', ), '_thumbnail_id' => array ( 0 => '3543', ), 'slide_template' => array ( 0 => 'default', ), '_wpb_vc_js_status' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'page_title_box_align' => array ( 0 => 'center', ), 'page_title_box_title_size' => array ( 0 => 'h1', ), 'page_title_box_bg_color' => array ( 0 => 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.65)', ), 'page_title_box_bg_image' => array ( 0 => '1716', ), 'page_title_box_text_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_box_line_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_box_subtitle_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_button_text' => array ( 0 => 'Button', ), 'page_title_button_url' => array ( 0 => '#', ), 'page_bc' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), '_wp_old_slug' => array ( 0 => 'the-trend-every-girl-should-wear-this-spring', 1 => 'jessica-krause-has-no-regrets-she-told-us-exactly-why-4', ), 'disable_post_sidebar' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'single_post_layout' => array ( 0 => '16', ), '_dp_original' => array ( 0 => '45', ), '_edit_last' => array ( 0 => '1', ), '_edit_lock' => array ( 0 => '1507545587:1', ), ), );
$pearl_page_personal_blog["about-me"] = array ( 'content' => '[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1506947846844{margin-bottom: 6px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_custom_heading source="post_title" font_container="tag:h1|text_align:center" use_theme_fonts="yes" css=".vc_custom_1506947747342{margin-top: 13px !important;margin-bottom: 8px !important;}"][stm_icon icon_align="center" height="8" icon="stmicon-blog_divider" css=".vc_custom_1506947817507{margin-bottom: 35px !important;}"][vc_column_text] <p style="text-align: center; line-height: 30px;"><span style="color: #595959;"><strong>Welcome! I’m Samantha Pearl, and this is my personal blog. I started my blog in 2013 with a mission to help people discover and refine their personal lifestyle. Now I share everything from family and travel to fashion, beauty, and home decor.</strong></span></p> [/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1506948998049{margin-bottom: 15px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="151" img_size="540x340" onclick="link_image"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" offset="vc_col-lg-4 vc_col-md-6"][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1506948591863{margin-top: 19px !important;}"] <p style="text-align: left; line-height: 30px; margin-bottom: 42px;">In 2016, people around the world spent 50 million hours on the site, which is more than 2 million days or 5.7 thousand years. And, what were people consuming in all that time? Everything.</p> <blockquote>I love connecting with you guys and sharing life’s beautiful journey a long the way.</blockquote> [/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1506949024967{margin-bottom: 29px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text] <p style="text-align: left; line-height: 30px;">Our content ranges from style trends and beauty DIYs to first person accounts from the political front lines, thought pieces on representation in media, advice from industry leaders on how to be a badass in the workplace, and more. From the bottom of my heart thank you for reading and following along! I read all your comments and truly enjoy connecting with you all!</p> [/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_custom_heading text="Contact me" font_container="tag:h2|text_align:center" use_theme_fonts="yes"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1506949065691{margin-bottom: 80px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][contact-form-7 id="156"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/6"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row_content_no_spaces" css=".vc_custom_1506660692996{margin-right: -30px !important;margin-bottom: -115px !important;margin-left: -30px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text][instagram-feed][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'meta' => array ( '_vc_post_settings' => array ( 0 => 'a:1:{s:10:"vc_grid_id";a:0:{}}', ), '_edit_lock' => array ( 0 => '1506949653:1', ), '_edit_last' => array ( 0 => '1', ), '_wp_page_template' => array ( 0 => 'default', ), '_wpb_vc_js_status' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'page_title_box_align' => array ( 0 => 'center', ), 'page_title_box_title_size' => array ( 0 => 'h1', ), 'page_title_box_bg_color' => array ( 0 => 'rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.65)', ), 'page_title_box_bg_image' => array ( 0 => '1716', ), 'page_title_box_text_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_box_line_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_box_subtitle_color' => array ( 0 => 'ffffff', ), 'page_title_button_text' => array ( 0 => 'Button', ), 'page_title_button_url' => array ( 0 => '#', ), 'page_bc' => array ( 0 => 'true', ), 'stm_sidebar_position' => array ( 0 => 'left', ), '_wpb_shortcodes_custom_css' => array ( 0 => '.vc_custom_1506947846844{margin-bottom: 6px !important;}.vc_custom_150694899